          <LEXSenses>
            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2021-11-26 20:32:48" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>a person who acts as a mediator in bringing about reconciliation{N:001}</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>mediator</Gloss>
                <Gloss>one who reconciles</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>A mediator may be spoken of in a number of different ways, often idiomatically, for example, ‘one who stands in the middle,’ ‘one who speaks to both,’ ‘one who cuts palavers,’ or ‘one who causes arguments to cease.’ It is also possible, however, to regard {L:μεσίτης&lt;SDBG:μεσίτης:000000&gt;} as being related to the process of causing agreement between the parties in question. For this aspect of the meaning of {L:μεσίτης&lt;SDBG:μεσίτης:000000&gt;}, see {D:31.22}.</Comments>
            </LEXSense>
